.TH "ks8851_rdreg" 9 "ks8851_rdreg" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ks8851_rdreg \- issue read register command and return the data
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" ks8851_rdreg
.BI "(struct ks8851_net *ks "  ","
.BI "unsigned int op "  ","
.BI "u8 *rxb "  ","
.BI "unsigned int rxl "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ks" 12
The device state
.IP "op" 12
The register address and byte enables in message format.
.IP "rxb" 12
The RX buffer to return the result into
.IP "rxl" 12
The length of data expected.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This is the low level read call that issues the necessary spi message(s)
to read data from the register specified in \fIop\fP.
